Tracks which context-node ids have already been injected/served during a Claude session, to deduplicate repeated hook firings on Read/Grep/Glob calls. State lives as one gitignored JSON file per session under `.context/.cache/hook-<sanitized-id>.json`.

`load` is intentionally fail-open: a missing or corrupt state file returns an empty `BTreeSet` rather than an error, so the hook's worst failure mode is re-injecting a node, never blocking. `save` is the only fallible entry point, returning `CtxError::Io` if serialization or the write fails.

`state_path(session: &str) -> RepoPath` sanitizes the session id by replacing any char outside `[A-Za-z0-9._-]` with `_` before building the cache filename — matters because session ids may come from environment variables with unexpected characters.

`ENV_SESSION_ID` (`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID`) is the env var read elsewhere (CLI path mode) to fold manually-served node ids into the same per-session ledger the `--hook` mode writes, so both code paths must agree on this constant and the state file naming scheme to stay deduplicated against each other.

Depends on `crate::env::Env` for testable file I/O abstraction and `crate::repo_path::RepoPath` for path construction rooted at repo root.